just one further comment. If we are likely to use the attrib plugin with a standard marker it might be repetitive and more typing to keep decorating as such:

```python

    @attrib(needs_proxy)
    def test_one(self):
        pass

    @attrib(needs_proxy)
    def test_two(self):
        pass
```

when we could consider having a simple:
```python
def needs_proxy(func):
    func.needs_proxy = True
    return func
```

making the test code:
```python
    @needs_proxy
    def test_one(self):
        pass

    @needs_proxy
    def test_two(self):
        pass
```

This could be arguably more explicit and nicer to look at and is certainly less code for the tester to write and wouldn't need an extra dependency on nose. Just a thought but is seems like there aren't too many drawbacks. 

