I recently had a similar problem with the font paths in 'font-awesome.css'. My solution was to invoke the 'grunt-string-replace' module inside of 'gruntfile.js' in order to update the paths.

First, install the required module:

    npm install grunt-string-replace --save-dev

Next, add the following snippet to 'gruntfile.js', update the options to suit your needs, register the task, and call it when you need to:

    'string-replace': {
        // Edit the file inline
        inline: {
            // Source and destination paths for 'font-awesome.css'
            files: {
                '_vendor/font-awesome/': '_vendor/font-awesome/**',
            },
            options: {
                replacements: [{
                    // Replacement pattern
                    pattern: /\.\.\/fonts/g,
                    // New font path
                    replacement: 'design/fonts'
                }]
            }
        }
    },

