@ilanschnell I've added it to `conda/exports.py` in #4729.  For all of your code that does `import conda`, try to confine the imports to `import conda.exports`.  That module is far more stable than the rest of the code base.  All of conda-build's imports are going through that module.  

conda-build is also isolating all of it's conda imports to a single location: https://github.com/conda/conda-build/blob/master/conda_build/conda_interface.py

And then the rest of the conda-build code imports everything through there.  That pattern has dramatically improved conda + conda-build inter-stability.

